personalInfo.education: University of Georgia (2015, Management Information Systems of Technology)

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Finished T5 at the British Columbia Q-School with rounds of 70-67-71-71, earning exempt status through the first six events...Mounted a final-round charge at the Staal Foundation Open with a 65 that included a dramatic eagle at the 72nd hole. Finished solo second to J.J. Spaun...Concluded the season 30th on the Order of Merit.
tourBios.personal: Favorite course he's played is Augusta National and wants to play Pine Valley...Favorite pro sports' team is the New York Jets...Dream foursome would include Bill Gates, Abraham Lincoln and Tiger Woods...Twitter is @nick_reach.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was 2nd in 2015 at the Staal Foundation Open presented by Tbaytel.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T72nd in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
